CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1965, pg. 7, reads: "King and Queen of the D.I.'s Mardi Gras Ball were chosen for their community as well as foreign activities. The king was Dr. H. Raymond Primas and the queen was Mrs. Edward Hale. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Dr. H. Raymond Primas and Barbara Hale wearing king and queen costumes, for D. I. Club's Mardi Gras Ball, Hilton Hotel
